@* THE CHILD whose @ChildContent sits BARE inside a region (register defect B3). The hole is the
   DIRECT body of the @if -- not wrapped in an element the child owns -- so when the parent's markup
   is inlined there it has no container to be inserted into. `Title` folds to the static string the
   parent supplied (decision 131's leaf-display path), so the @if is a real region.

   The SUPPORTED sibling is one element away: wrap the hole in an element the child declares
   (`@if (Title == "t") { <div id="hole">@ChildContent</div> }`, RegionHoleWrappedCard.razor), and
   the hole becomes a child of that element -- a stable container -- and it compiles. *@
<div id="card">@if (Title == "t") { @ChildContent }</div>

@code {
    [Parameter] public string Title { get; set; } = "";
    [Parameter] public RenderFragment? ChildContent { get; set; }
}
